, respectively). Similar results are displayed in Column (4), where all the variables are incorporated into the model. Column (5) shows the Variance Inflation Factor (VIF). These results support H1a but do not substantively support H1b and H1c. Ceteris paribus, and according to OLS estimation, increases of 1% in Digital ISS strategies would produce an increase of 0.68% in the innovation performance of firms.
